							That's really too vague a question. What are you trying to do? Learn about TCP/IP? BSD sockets? HTTP? Are yo trying to learn how to get data from the web and use it in some program you wish to write? &quot;communicating over a network&quot; is a very broad statement. And at this point, OSI is functionally a dead model (the IP stack won that war 15 or more years ago) even though it is often easier to teach communication theory that way.
