				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1738045">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							cURL (includes libcurl) is a nice little C client that does http and FTP protocols. It's been a few years since I code reviewed it for acceptance testing at my employer at the time, but I definitely felt like it was well organized, easy to use, and flexible. If you really want to learn raw socket programming, that's not a bad place to start.<br />
<br />
If you are looking at mobile, NSURLConnection is the workhorse for most applications in iOS networking needs (in some cases, you need to drop down to CF), I can't think offhand of anything that actually had to drop all the way down to sockets.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
