							Back in the dark ages, I wrote a socket re-router that would take port 80 telnet traffic and re-route it to another host - and then return the telnet data from the host to the original client via port 80.<br />
<br />
Taught me a LOT about sockets and whatnot.<br />
Creative ways of circumventing the university no-MUDing-policy, hooooo! <img src="images/smilies/grinyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Grin Yes" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
My point is just this: a well-defined, small learning project is a very good idea.
						</blockquote>
